  "response": "A typical high school basketball game usually lasts about 1.5 to 2 hours. Here\u2019s a breakdown of the timing:\n\n- **Game Duration:** High school basketball games are divided into four quarters, each lasting 8 minutes (32 minutes total playing time). Some states or leagues may use slightly different timings, such as four 10-minute quarters or two 16-minute halves.\n  \n- **Clock Stoppages:** The clock stops for various reasons, such as timeouts, fouls, free throws, and other game interruptions, which extends the total duration.\n\n- **Halftime:** There is typically a 10-minute halftime break between the second and third quarters.\n\n- **Timeouts:** Each team is usually allowed a certain number of timeouts (e.g., 3 full timeouts and 2 \"30-second\" timeouts), which can add to the total time.\n\n- **Overtime:** If the game is tied at the end of four quarters, overtime periods (usually 4 minutes each) are played until a winner is determined.\n\nKeep in mind that the actual duration can vary depending on the pace of the game, the number of fouls, and other factors.",
